OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1774278664
OL,3,C'Frenzied' knife attack suspect
OL,4,Cdetained by workers, court told
OL,6,FMr Bedloe said that on the morning of
OL,7,Fthe attack Ms Skeites was preparing
OL,8,Ffor a training presentation at the
OL,9,Ftravel agency where she worked when
OL,10,Fshe received a message that Ashraf was
OL,11,Foutside the building and had asked to
OL,12,Fsee her.
OL,14,FThe prosecutor said that Ms Skeites
OL,15,Fwent to meet him and after a "brief
OL,16,Fconversation, she told him to leave
OL,17,Fher along and go away" before
OL,18,F"randomly he hugged her", and then
OL,19,Ffollowed her back into the lobby.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1774278664
OL,3,C'Frenzied' knife attack suspect
OL,4,Cdetained by workers, court told
OL,6,FHe added: "She was telling him he
OL,7,Fneeded to leave. Suddenly he said: 'I
OL,8,Fhave a knife' and showed her a black-
OL,9,Fhandled kitchen knife."
OL,11,FMr Bedloe said that the victim later
OL,12,Fdescribed the attack saying: "Before I
OL,13,Fknew it, he was stabbing me."
OL,15,FHe continued: "She asked him to stop
OL,16,Fbut he didn't, then this frenzied
OL,17,Fattack stopped as soon as it started
OL,18,Fas other people came to help."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
